1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:01,540
Is that so?

2
00:00:01,540 --> 00:00:03,140
(Episode 100)

3
00:00:03,210 --> 00:00:06,340
You must have brought this
because you want to negotiate.

4
00:00:06,410 --> 00:00:08,480
I'm glad you're catching on so quickly.

5
00:00:09,310 --> 00:00:13,350
First, reinstate me as CEO and Jun Ho
as general manager immediately.

6
00:00:13,890 --> 00:00:15,990
And of course,
let me move back into this house.

7
00:00:16,050 --> 00:00:20,590
Also, those indictments accusing me
of child kidnapping,

8
00:00:20,930 --> 00:00:22,190
make them disappear.

9
00:00:30,270 --> 00:00:34,310
How dare you threaten me
with such ridiculous nonsense?

10
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:38,380
You really thought I'd fall for this?

11
00:00:39,440 --> 00:00:40,450
Fine.

12
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:44,980
Let's go to prison together.

13
00:00:46,450 --> 00:00:50,120
And we'll see who stays in there longer.

14
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:51,620
Care to bet?

15
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:54,630
Father.

16
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,460
If you go public,

17
00:00:57,730 --> 00:01:00,830
I'll reveal every single crime
you've committed...

18
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:02,900
and make sure you're legally punished.

19
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:06,400
Sure, it'll hurt me too.

20
00:01:06,970 --> 00:01:10,910
But don't forget I have plenty
of powerful allies in my corner.

21
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:15,850
I'm talking about all the powerful figures
who have a lot to lose if I go down.

22
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:20,820
You'll be hit a lot harder than I will.

23
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:24,560
Dream Group's reputation will take a hit,
along with Seo Rin's and Jang Mi's.

24
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:25,690
Really?

25
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,390
In that case,

26
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:32,000
your son, Jun Ho, won't just have
his reputation tarnished.

27
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,070
He'll be completely destroyed.

28
00:01:34,070 --> 00:01:35,170
In fact,

29
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:39,270
I can't even guarantee
he'll make it out of this alive.

30
00:01:41,570 --> 00:01:42,570
Alright.

31
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:46,880
Then just let me move back
into the house...

32
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:50,420
and allow me and Jun Ho
to be reinstated at the company.

33
00:01:51,050 --> 00:01:53,550
Father, you know what
Jun Ho and I are capable of.

34
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:57,020
I don't want Dream Group to collapse
any more than you do.

35
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:59,260
I've dedicated my life to this company.

36
00:01:59,690 --> 00:02:01,460
I'll allow you to move back into my house.

37
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:04,760
But don't even dream of getting
your CEO position at the hotel back.

38
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:08,230
- How dare you, when I can't trust you?
- Father.

39
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,470
You're going to start over
from the very bottom.

40
00:02:10,970 --> 00:02:12,800
Prove your worth from down there.

41
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:15,410
I'll be watching to see
if you'll be my loyal hound...

42
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:20,680
or a mad dog that turns
and bites my throat.

43
00:02:21,180 --> 00:02:25,080
Then I'll decide whether
to reinstate you as CEO.

44
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:29,720
Prove yourself with results.

45
00:02:30,590 --> 00:02:31,920
That's what you want too, isn't it?

46
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,160
And remember.

47
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:37,830
You have far more to lose than I do.

48
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:41,470
Understood.

49
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,340
Thank you for taking me back, Father.

50
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:47,910
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

51
00:02:51,510 --> 00:02:52,510
Seo Rin!

52
00:02:53,580 --> 00:02:54,850
What are you doing here all of a sudden?

53
00:02:57,180 --> 00:02:59,620
Seo Rin, what are you doing?

54
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:02,850
Enjoying yourself,
two-timing and flirting with every guy?

55
00:03:03,190 --> 00:03:05,090
Feel better now
that you've stolen another woman's man?

56
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:08,730
What are you talking about?
When have I ever two-timed anyone?

57
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:11,030
I saw it all.

58
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:13,500
I saw you in Jun Ho's arms.

59
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:16,430
You're not my sister anymore.
You're nothing to me.

60
00:03:16,870 --> 00:03:18,540
Don't you ever call us twins again.

61
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,940
Seo Rin. It's a misunderstanding.

62
00:03:21,010 --> 00:03:22,010
Shit!

63
00:03:22,540 --> 00:03:24,080
I never want to see you again.

64
00:03:26,950 --> 00:03:28,810
And I don't need a "mother"
anymore either.

65
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,520
I'm sending this mom back.

66
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,820
From now on, my only mother...

67
00:03:34,350 --> 00:03:36,550
is Chae Hwa Young. Got it?

68
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,020
Chae Hwa Young is our enemy!

69
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:39,320
She's your enemy, not mine.

70
00:03:39,790 --> 00:03:42,230
To me, she's the mother
who raised me for 30 years.

71
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:45,400
So don't push it on me. Got it?

72
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,770
Don't think about looking for evidence
or any of that again.

73
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:51,370
Seo Rin!

74
00:03:59,210 --> 00:04:00,510
Hello? Aunt Geum Soon.

75
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,480
What did you say?

76
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:06,120
You're saying Grandpa let Chae Hwa Young
back into the house?

77
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,190
Don't you think we gave up too much
in that negotiation?

78
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:12,860
It's fine for now.
We got our foot in the door.

79
00:04:13,630 --> 00:04:16,130
It's taking one step back
to move 100 steps forward.

80
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:21,300
I completely underestimated
that old man Chairman Ma.

81
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,970
So, he found out Jun Ho is my son.

82
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:27,810
He's having a grand time
holding Jun Ho hostage.

83
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:31,540
You served Chairman Ma for 30 years,

84
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:35,980
so it's no surprise
he knows you just as well.

85
00:04:42,650 --> 00:04:44,990
As if letting her back into the house
wasn't bad enough,

86
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:46,690
you're letting her back
into the company too?

87
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:49,290
How could you do this, Grandfather?

88
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:53,770
You know full well what that woman did
to my mom and to us.

89
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,840
- Is this about your revenge?
- Revenge?

90
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,500
This is about justice.

91
00:04:59,770 --> 00:05:02,510
A criminal must pay for their crime.

92
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:05,540
Chae Hwa Young got away with her crimes.

93
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:06,540
You're right.

94
00:05:07,180 --> 00:05:09,980
I'm not saying I don't understand
how you feel.

95
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:15,090
But as the former CEO of Dream Hotel,

96
00:05:15,150 --> 00:05:18,890
we can't ignore the contributions
and connections Chae Hwa Young has made.

97
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:23,060
A company isn't run on emotions.

98
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,160
I know.

99
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,730
I know the company is your top priority,
Grandfather.

100
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:31,040
So you mean you'll cover up her crimes
for the company's sake?

101
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,800
That's not what I'm saying.

102
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,910
I'm not bringing Chae Hwa Young
back to work under me.

103
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,640
I'm bringing her back to work under you.

104
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:42,810
- What?
- I'm putting Chae Hwa Young under you,

105
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:44,880
as an entry-level employee.

106
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:48,720
You need to prove your own abilities
to Chae Hwa Young.

107
00:05:49,190 --> 00:05:53,760
Dominate her with your skills
so she won't dare say a word to you.

108
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:56,290
It won't be too late
to cast her out after that.

109
00:05:57,360 --> 00:06:00,260
There's a proper order to everything.

110
00:06:00,930 --> 00:06:04,140
That's the only way the board of directors
will respect you.

111
00:06:05,140 --> 00:06:06,140
Right.

112
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:09,470
I will prove that my management skills
are far superior to Chae Hwa Young's.

113
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,380
And then,

114
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:15,080
I'll prove you wrong for thinking
you can't get rid of her.

115
00:06:15,850 --> 00:06:18,780
And I will gather evidence
in my own way...

116
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:21,550
and make sure Chae Hwa Young
is brought to justice.

117
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:25,890
Good. Now that's my granddaughter.

118
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,060
Remember.

119
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,300
Keep your friends close,

120
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:35,200
but your enemies even closer.

121
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:39,500
That way, you can strike them down
at any moment.

122
00:06:49,110 --> 00:06:51,080
Jun Ho, you're here.

123
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:54,990
You mean you're being reinstated?

124
00:06:55,050 --> 00:06:56,090
That's right.

125
00:06:56,350 --> 00:07:00,220
I told you I'd be back at the company,
didn't I?

126
00:07:00,790 --> 00:07:02,090
I'm a woman of my word.

127
00:07:02,290 --> 00:07:04,600
The Chairman told her to start tomorrow.

128
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,300
Starting tomorrow?

129
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:09,600
Jun Ho,
we need to brace ourselves from now on.

130
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:14,670
We're at the point where it's either eat
or be eaten by that old man.

131
00:07:15,410 --> 00:07:19,340
We have to work together
and get Dream in the palm of our hands.

132
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:38,100
Director Ma, the person working with us
starting today...

133
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:41,800
I mean, this is our new employee,
Chae Hwa Young.

134
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,910
Welcome, Chae Hwa Young.

135
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:56,950
Where's your employee ID?

136
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:05,090
Is your IQ so low
that you don't know to wear your ID?

137
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,320
Put it on.

138
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:09,660
Every employee needs to know
their former CEO is...

139
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,400
now a junior employee.

140
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,270
Goodness, I'm so scared.

141
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,070
Don't you understand
your superior's orders?

142
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,800
Put it around your neck.

143
00:08:19,370 --> 00:08:22,340
Come on, Chae Hwa Young.
You knew this was coming.

144
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:23,770
I have to endure this.

145
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:32,280
(Employee Chae Hwa Young)

146
00:08:34,550 --> 00:08:35,950
Employee Chae Hwa Young.

147
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:38,060
It suits you better than I thought.

148
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:41,290
Good morning.

149
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:43,930
- Morning.
- CEO Chae.

150
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:45,260
Good morning.

151
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:47,870
(Employee Chae Hwa Young)

152
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,500
Kim Shin Yul. Choi Seo Eun.

153
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,270
Now that everyone's here,
let's prepare for the meeting.

154
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:53,770
Yes, ma'am.

155
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,180
Team Leader Jin, go
to General Manager Kang Jun Ho's office.

156
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,580
Help him pack up his desk.

157
00:09:02,050 --> 00:09:03,050
Excuse me?

158
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,250
Yes.

159
00:09:09,490 --> 00:09:11,490
What is she up to, sending everyone out?

160
00:09:12,190 --> 00:09:15,660
Oh Jang Mi, are you setting the stage
to really have a go at me?

161
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:18,960
You're really starting to sound
like my boss.

162
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,700
Don't get cocky, Oh Jang Mi.

163
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,130
Listen to that.

164
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,670
Such a rotten attitude
for a junior employee.

165
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,640
How dare you tell your superior
"don't get cocky"?

166
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:30,510
Do you still not get the situation?

167
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:34,080
Chae Hwa Young,
I'm the one holding your leash now.

168
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:35,850
You're getting a real kick out of this,
aren't you?

169
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:38,820
Thrilled you get to put me in my place,
aren't you?

170
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:41,850
Fine. Go on, mock me all you want.

171
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:43,850
If you harass me,

172
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:47,630
I'll plaster it all over the Internet
as workplace harassment by a superior.

173
00:09:47,690 --> 00:09:49,590
Is that so?

174
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,730
Go on, try it. This should be interesting.

175
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:56,330
"Former CEO Chae Hwa Young, Now a Junior,
Abused by Her Superior."

176
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,500
If a huge headline like that
starts making the rounds online,

177
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,110
the clicks will be off the charts.

178
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:03,610
If you want to do it, do it.

179
00:10:04,140 --> 00:10:05,340
It should be fascinating.

180
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:06,710
Oh Jang Mi.

181
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:10,150
Just tell me
what I'm supposed to do already.

182
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:11,820
This is a professional workplace,

183
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:15,320
so address me with the proper respect,
Ms. Chae Hwa Young.

184
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:18,320
What would you like me to do?

185
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:22,190
We have a project briefing today,
so start by prepping the conference room.

186
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:25,400
And get some coffee ready, too.

187
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,300
What?

188
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:30,330
- What are you telling me to do?
- Coffee.

189
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:33,700
Are you getting hard of hearing
in your old age now?

190
00:10:34,170 --> 00:10:36,210
I said to prepare the coffee,
Ms. Chae Hwa Young.

191
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:37,740
You always make me repeat myself.

192
00:10:38,610 --> 00:10:39,780
Make sure it doesn't happen again.

193
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,150
Our junior employee, Ms. Chae Hwa Young.

194
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:51,290
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

195
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:59,460
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

196
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,400
What made you decide to come back?

197
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:06,270
Tons of other companies would love
to have someone like you.

198
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:07,270
Why?

199
00:11:07,610 --> 00:11:09,140
You scared I'm going to steal your girl?

200
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,470
Jun Ho, what's gotten into you?

201
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,540
I'm going to try and get back together
with Jang Mi,

202
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:16,050
so please stay out of it, Kang Baek Ho.

203
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,680
Don't be ridiculous.

204
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:20,580
That's what you want.
It's not what Jang Mi wants.

205
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,250
And how can you be so sure about that?

206
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:25,060
Are you able to read her mind now?

207
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:27,260
Jun Ho, please just stop this.

208
00:11:27,930 --> 00:11:28,930
Just you watch.

209
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:32,700
- You'll see how I win Jang Mi back.
- I get how you feel,

210
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:36,270
but if you give my woman a hard time,
I won't forgive you, even as my brother.

211
00:11:44,110 --> 00:11:46,240
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

212
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,810
This is so frustrating.

213
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:52,620
Why is Baek Ho so crazy about Oh Jang Mi!

214
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:54,550
My mother even said she supports...

215
00:11:55,450 --> 00:11:56,590
and is rooting
for Jang Mi and Baek Ho's love.

216
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:00,490
Jun Ho.
Don't you dare give up on Oh Jang Mi.

217
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,760
I'm not giving up on Baek Ho, either.

218
00:12:03,990 --> 00:12:06,460
I'm going to do whatever it takes,
so I have no regrets.

219
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:16,240
(Employee Chae Hwa Young)

220
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:22,310
Goodness.

221
00:12:22,980 --> 00:12:25,050
Shouldn't someone
help her with the coffee?

222
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,480
Ma'am, let me get that...

223
00:12:27,490 --> 00:12:28,520
Hello.

224
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:30,190
Employee Chae Hwa Young.

225
00:12:34,930 --> 00:12:37,430
As you can see, I'm doing just fine.

226
00:12:41,270 --> 00:12:44,270
Chae Hwa Young, you can't break down now.

227
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,600
Think of Jun Ho.

228
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,970
You have to get through this
for your son, Jun Ho.

229
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,000
(Sand Lance Fish Sauce)

230
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:17,430
Let's see how you like a taste of this.

231
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:24,380
Oh Jang Mi.

232
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:26,940
How dare she make me go on a coffee run?

233
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,180
Go on. Drink up.

234
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,320
Honey.

235
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:38,390
Making Chae Hwa Young
a junior employee was one thing,

236
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,160
but I can't believe
she's already back in the house.

237
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:44,830
It's like a bad toothache
flaring up all over again.

238
00:13:45,330 --> 00:13:47,030
- Darn it.
- Yeom San Wol.

239
00:13:49,770 --> 00:13:51,170
Did you go through my things?

240
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:53,670
Touch your stuff?
I'm not some common thief.

241
00:13:53,770 --> 00:13:55,310
Why would I touch your stuff?

242
00:13:55,410 --> 00:13:58,140
What's missing, sweetheart?

243
00:13:58,210 --> 00:13:59,740
My lipstick.

244
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,210
Lipstick?

245
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,580
I really need that.

246
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,010
Shit.

247
00:14:08,550 --> 00:14:10,990
- Chairman.
- Yes. Come on in.

248
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:14,020
So, you had something to tell me?

249
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,360
Are you...

250
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:20,100
also upset I brought
CEO Chae back into the company?

251
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,370
No, that's not it.

252
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,040
Chairman.

253
00:14:25,540 --> 00:14:27,470
I want to marry Jang Mi.

254
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:30,940
What? Jang Mi?

255
00:14:31,180 --> 00:14:33,110
It hasn't been long since she broke
her engagement with my brother,

256
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,480
and the legal papers aren't finalized,
so I'm sure you'll object, but...

257
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:37,450
Yes, marry her.

258
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:38,880
I'm sorry?

259
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,380
Are you...

260
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:42,950
really giving your blessing
to marry Jang Mi?

261
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:44,050
I am.

262
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:48,730
I've been watching you and Jang Mi
for a while now.

263
00:14:50,630 --> 00:14:53,100
I don't want to make
the same mistake again.

264
00:14:53,830 --> 00:14:56,170
People who love each other
should be together.

265
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:57,840
Go ahead and get married.

266
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:00,500
Thank you, Chairman.

267
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:05,310
Chairman,
I swear, I'll never make Jang Mi cry.

268
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:06,640
I'll make her happy,
and we'll live a good life.

269
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:10,810
Okay, that's enough.
You can let go of my hand now, all right?

270
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:11,880
Right.

271
00:15:15,450 --> 00:15:17,760
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

272
00:15:17,890 --> 00:15:19,620
Goodness, what is all this?

273
00:15:20,090 --> 00:15:22,590
Looks like you packed it
with all of the Chairman's favorites.

274
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,660
They're for Jang Mi's grandfather.

275
00:15:24,930 --> 00:15:28,200
I'm going to apologize to him.

276
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,270
Jang Mi and Seo Rin will be happy
to hear that, Mom.

277
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,840
Jang Mi is pretty. Tok Hee is pretty.

278
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:36,510
And Suk Hee is brilliant.

279
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,650
From now on,
let's stop focusing on our image...

280
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,320
and start focusing on the numbers.

281
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:54,060
Let's hold off
on the emotional marketing for now.

282
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:00,160
Go on, drink it. Drink it right now.

283
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:05,100
The problem is our weekday vacancy rate.

284
00:16:08,770 --> 00:16:10,710
Come on. Just drink it!

285
00:16:11,010 --> 00:16:13,910
Go on and make a scene
in front of everyone.

286
00:16:14,510 --> 00:16:16,050
Let them all laugh at you.

287
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:19,980
Director Ma, this is due to
the drop in our occupancy rate.

288
00:16:20,380 --> 00:16:21,550
The reason is perfectly clear.

289
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:26,690
It's because we lost important clients
due to the former CEO's misconduct.

290
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:31,430
Chae Hwa Young?

291
00:16:33,230 --> 00:16:34,230
Chae Hwa Young!

292
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:35,630
What?

293
00:16:37,570 --> 00:16:38,570
Yes.

294
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:42,210
Do you have any alternative solutions
for improving our hotel's performance?

295
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:44,880
In here, we're not mother and daughter.

296
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:46,880
I'm going to keep things
strictly professional.

297
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,680
That way, we won't disrupt the workflow
for the rest of the staff.

298
00:16:50,380 --> 00:16:52,980
Chae Hwa Young.
Let's hear your alternative solution.

299
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:54,950
And try not to get distracted.

300
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,190
I think we should run a promotion.

301
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:58,320
You sound pretty confident.

302
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:00,490
Yes, I am.

303
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:03,490
Fine. Then, instead of
a discount promotion,

304
00:17:03,930 --> 00:17:05,200
let's secure corporate accounts.

305
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:08,430
- Annual contracts. How does that sound?
- You want me to?

306
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,570
Since you're the one who started
this whole mess,

307
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:12,500
you should be the one to clean it up.

308
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:15,640
I mean, you suggested the promotion
because you were so confident, right?

309
00:17:16,370 --> 00:17:17,370
Fine.

310
00:17:18,540 --> 00:17:20,640
All right. I'm confident I can do it.

311
00:17:21,110 --> 00:17:23,450
Great. In that case,
shall we have a toast?

312
00:17:23,950 --> 00:17:26,320
To welcome back Chae Hwa Young
and to wish her well.

313
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:28,620
- What do you all say?
- Sounds good.

314
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:31,320
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

315
00:17:44,370 --> 00:17:45,840
Wait, what happened?

316
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:48,010
Why is the sand lance fish sauce
in my drink?

317
00:17:48,370 --> 00:17:51,980
Are you okay?
Hwa Young, I really enjoyed the coffee.

318
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:54,240
Thanks.

319
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:16,700
Chae Hwa Young, did you forget
my family owns a side dish shop?

320
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:19,040
How dare you spike my drink
with sand lance fish sauce?

321
00:18:20,870 --> 00:18:21,870
Chae Hwa Young.

322
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,840
Go and make another copy of this for me.

323
00:18:27,610 --> 00:18:28,780
I seem to have scribbled
all over this one.

324
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:30,710
Hurry back before the meeting starts.

325
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:51,870
Thanks for making work so entertaining,
Chae Hwa Young.

326
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:54,040
I can't wait to see what you do next.

327
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:08,220
Baek Ho, what's going on?
Why did you want to see me at work?

328
00:19:09,090 --> 00:19:12,320
Jang Mi!
The Chairman finally gave us his blessing.

329
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:15,260
He did?
What permission did your grandfather give?

330
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:19,360
For us to get married.
He's given us his official blessing.

331
00:19:22,670 --> 00:19:24,070
It feels like a dream.

332
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:26,100
I can't believe I get to marry you.

333
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:30,670
Chairman Ma approved of
Jang Mi and Kang Baek Ho's marriage?

334
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:33,440
The timing couldn't be better
to get Seo Rin and Jun Ho...

335
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:35,750
to finally make a move.

336
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:44,720
This is a workplace, not a dating spot,

337
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:47,060
Director Ma and Lawyer Kang.

338
00:19:47,290 --> 00:19:50,590
Hearing that from a mere employee like you
really brightens my day.

339
00:19:51,060 --> 00:19:53,660
Continue to address me as "Director Ma."

340
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:06,880
Alright, Baek Ho. My goodness.

341
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,610
The Chairman has really outdone himself.

342
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:12,280
This should be fun to watch.

343
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:15,920
To think that Chae Hwa Young came back
as a junior employee.

344
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:19,460
Chairman Ma is really something else.

345
00:20:19,690 --> 00:20:22,760
Taking her down a peg like that.

346
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:24,930
A junior employee?

347
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,960
Right, Baek Ho.

348
00:20:27,260 --> 00:20:31,400
It's a relief your brother wasn't demoted.

349
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:32,740
Although...

350
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:36,210
I wouldn't be surprised
if his birth mother pulled some strings.

351
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:41,410
Don't push yourself too hard.

352
00:20:41,980 --> 00:20:43,350
All right, talk soon.

353
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:46,450
What is it?

354
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,950
Does your heart break to hear that...

355
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:53,190
Chae Hwa Young is suffering
as a junior employee?

356
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:55,360
You never used to be this kind of person.

357
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:58,230
The Han Young Ja I used to know...

358
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:02,000
wasn't the kind of woman
who'd rejoice in someone else's misery.

359
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,830
And the Kang Nam Bong I used to know...

360
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:05,900
wasn't the kind of man...

361
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:09,510
who would cruelly betray me
and stab me in the back.

362
00:21:10,110 --> 00:21:13,380
He wasn't a fool so smitten with a vixen
that he couldn't think straight.

363
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:16,450
He wasn't a pathetic fool like that.

364
00:21:17,180 --> 00:21:19,280
- That's enough.
- People don't just change...

365
00:21:19,650 --> 00:21:21,050
for no reason.

366
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:22,790
It's a reaction to how they're treated.

367
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,090
This is suffocating.

368
00:21:24,090 --> 00:21:26,620
When will you stop?
If this continues, let's get a divorce.

369
00:21:26,690 --> 00:21:27,690
Divorce?

370
00:21:27,820 --> 00:21:29,530
I will never grant you a divorce.

371
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:32,030
Don't even think about leaving this house.

372
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,630
The moment you walk out that door,

373
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:37,170
I'll leak Chae Hwa Young's corruption
to the press.

374
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:38,600
You'll what?

375
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:40,400
You're not going anywhere.

376
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,810
You'll stay right here by my side
and be tormented.

377
00:21:43,170 --> 00:21:47,180
You're frightening.
It's scary how much a person can change.

378
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,480
I really had no idea.

379
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:49,810
And another thing...

380
00:21:50,410 --> 00:21:52,050
I'm not going to live like I used to.

381
00:21:53,050 --> 00:21:55,590
- What?
- Because you couldn't have children,

382
00:21:55,590 --> 00:21:58,320
I adopted Jun Ho and Baek Ho as my own.

383
00:21:58,690 --> 00:22:03,590
And I've spent my whole life treating you
like I'd give you the moon and the stars.

384
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:05,500
And that life I built...

385
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:08,200
has been completely destroyed.

386
00:22:09,830 --> 00:22:10,830
From now on,

387
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:12,840
I'm going to live
a completely different life.

388
00:22:13,370 --> 00:22:14,440
Just you watch.

389
00:22:16,470 --> 00:22:19,180
Where do you think you're going
dressed like that?

390
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,510
None of your business.

391
00:22:22,180 --> 00:22:24,310
You get to fool around
with Chae Hwa Young,

392
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:26,480
so did you really think
I'd just sit back and take it?

393
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:34,930
Unbelievable.

394
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,000
The nerve of her.

395
00:22:42,430 --> 00:22:45,770
Seo Rin has dozens of lipsticks,
and I only took a few of them.

396
00:22:45,970 --> 00:22:47,300
Does she really need to throw such a fit?

397
00:22:48,570 --> 00:22:50,410
She has a good memory, I'll give her that.

398
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:52,540
Remembering exactly how many she had.

399
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:01,250
Well, hello there.

400
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:05,520
I called you yesterday,
but they said you were on the golf course.

401
00:23:05,660 --> 00:23:07,920
And what business might you have with me?

402
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:11,960
Well, you're the one
who's always in the know.

403
00:23:14,630 --> 00:23:15,730
It's about my husband.

404
00:23:16,470 --> 00:23:19,570
I was wondering if you knew anything
about his first wife.

405
00:23:23,610 --> 00:23:25,510
What is it, Mom?
I'm busy, so make it quick.

406
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:28,280
What?

407
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:30,580
Wait a second.

408
00:23:37,990 --> 00:23:39,290
You found out about Seong Sil,

409
00:23:39,290 --> 00:23:41,120
the woman the Chairman called
in his sleep?

410
00:23:42,090 --> 00:23:44,490
- Who is she?
- We were right.

411
00:23:44,490 --> 00:23:46,960
She was his first wife.
Her name is Lee Seong Sil.

412
00:23:47,260 --> 00:23:49,700
So the woman in that photo
was his first wife.

413
00:23:50,170 --> 00:23:54,240
But get this, they say the Chairman lost
both his daughter and his first wife.

414
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:56,510
He lost both his daughter
and his first wife?

415
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:59,240
The Chairman had a daughter?

416
00:24:01,780 --> 00:24:02,950
Apparently so.

417
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:07,050
Besides, what's the point
of being jealous...

418
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:08,420
of his dead wife and daughter?

419
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:12,390
So you must've been worried
a new love rival had shown up.

420
00:24:13,060 --> 00:24:14,060
But still,

421
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:17,790
that woman's face looks so familiar.

422
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,730
I'm sure I've seen her somewhere before.

423
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,200
Okay, Mom, I get it. I have to go.

424
00:24:28,370 --> 00:24:29,370
CEO Chae.

425
00:24:29,870 --> 00:24:30,870
What was that all about?

426
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:34,310
What's this about Chairman Ma
having a daughter other than Dong Seok?

427
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:38,750
Are you going to tell me or not?

428
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:43,450
Fine. I have some news
you'll find very interesting.

429
00:24:44,590 --> 00:24:45,760
What news is that?

430
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:48,860
- Is it about Baek Ho?
- You go first.

431
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:51,130
What's this about Chairman Ma
having a daughter?

432
00:24:55,070 --> 00:24:57,870
This is a picture the Chairman
was secretly looking at in his study.

433
00:25:00,270 --> 00:25:01,570
Send me this picture.

434
00:25:01,910 --> 00:25:03,170
Now it's your turn, CEO Chae.

435
00:25:03,940 --> 00:25:06,010
What about Baek Ho? Tell me, quickly.

436
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:09,080
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

437
00:25:11,050 --> 00:25:13,650
Jun Ho.
This is no time to be sitting around.

438
00:25:14,350 --> 00:25:17,420
The Chairman gave Oh Jang Mi and Baek Ho
his blessing to get married.

439
00:25:19,420 --> 00:25:21,020
Are you just going to
stand by and do nothing?

440
00:25:21,220 --> 00:25:22,430
Did I say that?

441
00:25:23,260 --> 00:25:24,260
Just you wait.

442
00:25:39,780 --> 00:25:42,250
Grandfather, we're here.

443
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:43,980
You're here.

444
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:48,550
What brings you here?

445
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:54,360
My mom wanted to come and apologize
for what happened last time.

446
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:57,860
What? Why is Jung Suk Hee
at my house again?

447
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:03,500
Suk Hee is sorry.

448
00:26:04,030 --> 00:26:08,370
Suk Hee is sorry for breaking the cup.
Suk Hee yelled.

449
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:10,070
Suk Hee was bad.

450
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:13,980
All right, I get it. That's enough.

451
00:26:17,850 --> 00:26:20,550
This is a picture the Chairman
was secretly looking at in his study.

452
00:26:34,060 --> 00:26:37,270
Which baby should I take?

453
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:48,080
It's just a common four-leaf clover.

454
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:50,480
No, it can't be.

455
00:26:50,750 --> 00:26:52,820
No way. That's impossible.

456
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,800
It has to be here somewhere.

457
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:08,430
I'm sure...

458
00:27:08,870 --> 00:27:11,000
it had a four-leaf clover
embroidered on it.

459
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:12,670
I have to make sure.

460
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:48,170
It's exactly the same.

461
00:27:48,940 --> 00:27:49,970
Then that means...

462
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:53,080
Jung Suk Hee is Chairman Ma's daughter?

463
00:28:24,740 --> 00:28:26,310
(The First Man)

464
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:30,610
So this is why you've been
Chae Hwa Young's lapdog?

465
00:28:31,080 --> 00:28:32,520
I won't let you two get away with this.

466
00:28:32,950 --> 00:28:35,320
What kind of junior employee
can't even handle this?

467
00:28:35,690 --> 00:28:37,350
- Do it over.
- What?

468
00:28:37,420 --> 00:28:38,760
I said, do it over.

469
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:41,830
Your daughter,
who we all thought was dead,

470
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,990
is alive.

471
00:28:43,990 --> 00:28:46,700
My Eun Hye is alive?

472
00:28:51,130 --> 00:28:53,140
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
